narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you're going to take a language class, take Latin over ancient greek, and take it with Tristan Taylor.

I would warn the student that the class moves very quickly and is very intensive, and that a lot of work will be required to keep up in the class. I really enjoyed the teacher that I had, so I can not speak for other sections, but I would tell them only to take the class if they are willing to work hard and be dedicated.
A pretty fun course if you don't know any Latin and are curious. You will learn most of the entire grammar system. Shop a few instructors first.
The course is intense. You cover a lot of material in a short time, but it is certainly worthwhile. To avoid cramming Sunday nights for the Monday quizzes, do a little each day.
